Widespread flooding as a result of Cyclone Eloise claimed its first life in the Lowveld on Sunday when a five-year-old boy was swept away while his mother tried to cross a river in Masoyi. On Monday morning, the police’s diving unit, Off-Road Rescue Unit and Rescue SA launched a search for a 40-year-old man who had disappeared under the water in a stretch of the Blyde River near Pilgrim’s Rest. He is presumed to have drowned. ALSO READ: Cyclone Eloise claims young boy as first victim Witnesses say the man, whose identity is still unknown, was trying to cross the river when he was swept away by a strong current. More flood warnings have been issued and people are advised to remain cautious over the strong flow of rivers and streams. This is a developing story and more information will be supplied as soon as it becomes available. 